Instruction: With a known-good 12 V applied from the PSU (switches ON), sequentially test continuity of the main 12 V line and 0 V return from the input of Control Module 1 through to the input of the load module. Disconnect the downstream chain and, module by module, verify that each pair of ‘through’ cables is internally connected (switch closed) and that 12 V appears on the output pair when present on the input pair. Also verify continuity through the series diode in the load module in the forward direction and open in reverse. This will locate any open circuit in the series path (e.g., miswired fast-connect pair, open trace, failed switch, or open diode) that prevents current from reaching the control LEDs and lamp.
