ACTION:
With PSU and Control Module 1 reconnected and its switch set to ON, measure the voltage on both cables of the output pair of Control Module 1 relative to the PSU negative (0 V). Then toggle the switch OFF and ON while observing the voltage. This checks whether the internal through‑connection and switch of Control Module 1 correctly pass the 12 V line to its output pair and reveals any open circuit inside the first control module.
