2026-04-21 01:27:43 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=["Control Module 3: internal 12 V input connection at port 'n' (floating/disconnected end of Control Input Cable (+) 3)"] hypothesis_explanation="Measurements show that Control Input Cable (+) 3 is at ~12 V, and its internal path to the output (+) and the indicator branch (resistor and LED) all have nominal continuity when checked directly. However, the diagnostic explicitly reports that the end of the 12 V input node at port 'n' of Control Input Cable (+) 3 is floating/disconnected. This means that, under actual operation, the external input 12 V is not electrically bonded to the internal 12 V node feeding the through‑path and LED. As a result, no 12 V appears at the output pair of Control Module 3, its indicator LED stays off, and all downstream modules and the load receive no power. The root cause is therefore an open connection at the 12 V input interface of Control Module 3 (e.g., broken solder joint, loose terminal, or damaged trace) between the physical cable termination and the internal circuit node. Repairing or re‑terminating this connection should restore 12 V propagation through module 3 and allow LEDs and the lamp to operate, assuming no additional faults downstream."
